snippet.textDisplay:
one of the power's creators said "we want to give our fans the most of of they want".
Well, I hope you know that everybody wants to see Ghost return, and not just flashes, memories etc.: ALIVE!
You better show us in power 2 a 3 minutes scene from inside the Truth (that has been hidden from us) where the police woman arrives there, sees ghost unconscious, checks his pulse, sees he's still alive, arranges for him to be taken to emergency through the back door and puts him under high security. Then she tells all the policeman outside not to allow anybody inside the club and to announce his death (hence, the policeman who doesnt allow Tariq to see his father's dead body). Then we see Ghost in coma (and only WE know he is alive/ no characters know), and we see a staged funeral with a closed casket, and everybody continuing with their lives, up until the end of the power 2 which shows Ghost coming back from the coma, and then the game/ revenge/ you owe me type of episodes begin, with a call to Tommy telling him "Im back": The end of the series and the beginning of the 3rd. :D
You said it yourself producers "Ghost always wins" so stick to that. :)
And I guess most fans would love you if you would do this.

Ps: if this whole thing could be done in the last episode of power 2, would be better. Making us think he is dead, and then show this scenario in the end.
Ps.2: You brought Kenan back from the dead, so you could do the same for Ghost.
Ps.3: Comon, didnt you see by now that 99% of the fans dont like Tariq caracther much, we all want to see him pay.

Finally, Ive seen so many ways to bring back a character that you could even show from the beginning a funeral, open casket, Ghost inside being dead, bury him and all. And still bring him back, because I saw in other series a staged funeral with the help of some drug that keeps the person alive, but unconscious, and fake the pulse. You could show us all of this, and make us think he's really dead, and still show how the whole thing was staged in the series finale. I think it would be a great surprise for all of us. :)

snippet.textDisplay:
I want Ghost in the show or Tommy Spin Off. Ghost deserved to get out the game and it looks like they used him to be on some “Toxic Masculinity” BS. I went back and watched season 5 & you can admire his heart. It’s like they sacrificed Season 6 to be a pilot rollout for the spin-offs.

I’m not sure why they didn’t have Omari on Power Confidential but something isn’t right. I remember watching promo for the Season 6 premier and could see Lela and Omari both looked unhappy (watch the Sway In The Morning Interview). ..I’m sorry Starz, to not a have a funeral to end the chapter maybe in hopes fans will speculate if Ghost somehow survived, but they tricked the audience & Courtney seems to not ever agree with fans but we are the people who watch the show. If Book 2 does not do well, they will Axe all the subsequent shows and do another “Comcast is about to drop Starz” ..trust me, if these endings leaked wayyy in advance, people wouldn’t have continued watching. I feel like I got raped & tricked with this ending. Killing Angie was already disrespectful, but how they handled Omari Hardwick ..salutes to him for being a professional, but it’s reflecting on the show in a BAD WAY.

I’m beyond disappointed how they treated their leading man.🤦🏾‍♂️ He literally on all your posters and they treated him like he DID NOT make the show what it is. No Awards just pure raw talent.
snippet.textOriginal:
I want Ghost in the show or Tommy Spin Off. Ghost deserved to get out the game and it looks like they used him to be on some “Toxic Masculinity” BS. I went back and watched season 5 & you can admire his heart. It’s like they sacrificed Season 6 to be a pilot rollout for the spin-offs.

I’m not sure why they didn’t have Omari on Power Confidential but something isn’t right. I remember watching promo for the Season 6 premier and could see Lela and Omari both looked unhappy (watch the Sway In The Morning Interview). ..I’m sorry Starz, to not a have a funeral to end the chapter maybe in hopes fans will speculate if Ghost somehow survived, but they tricked the audience & Courtney seems to not ever agree with fans but we are the people who watch the show. If Book 2 does not do well, they will Axe all the subsequent shows and do another “Comcast is about to drop Starz” ..trust me, if these endings leaked wayyy in advance, people wouldn’t have continued watching. I feel like I got raped & tricked with this ending. Killing Angie was already disrespectful, but how they handled Omari Hardwick ..salutes to him for being a professional, but it’s reflecting on the show in a BAD WAY. 

I’m beyond disappointed how they treated their leading man.🤦🏾‍♂️ He literally on all your posters and they treated him like he DID NOT make the show what it is. No Awards just pure raw talent.
